==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*-dēdi-'', from Indo-European ''*dʰēti-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[dad|dād]]'' (Dutch ''[[daad]]''), Old High German ''[[tat|tāt]]'' (German ''[[Tat]]''), Old Norse ''[[dáð]]'' (Swedish ''[[dåd]]''), Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐌳𐌴𐌸𐍃]].  The PIE root is also the source of Greek ''[[θέσις]]'', Latin ''[[conditio]]''.

